# ── Nedavate booking links (Cal.com) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and replace with your real Cal.com links.
#
# 1. Create a free account at https://cal.com
# 2. Create two event types:
#      • "Free Strategy Call" (20 min, no price)
#      • "AI Strategy Session" (60 min) — install the Stripe app in Cal.com and
#        enable payment on this event so visitors pay when they book.
# 3. The link below is the part after cal.com/  e.g.  "neda/free-strategy-call".
#
# While testing, you can point both at the same free event.

NEXT_PUBLIC_CAL_FREE_LINK=your-username/free-strategy-call
NEXT_PUBLIC_CAL_PAID_LINK=your-username/ai-strategy-session

# ── Lead magnet email capture (optional but recommended) ──────────────────────
# The checklist signup form (/api/subscribe) forwards emails to ONE of these.
# Pick whichever you use. If none are set, the form still works in dev but the
# email is NOT stored (a warning is logged).
#
# Option A — ConvertKit (set both):
# CONVERTKIT_API_KEY=your_convertkit_api_key
# CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=1234567
#
# Option B — Generic webhook (Zapier / Make / n8n / Google Sheet, etc.):
# LEAD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/xxxx/yyyy
